'The Human Union' is the name given to the ideal of a global movement of co-operative human beings who wish to harness the technology of P2P and social networking into an administrative system that could, in theory, replace old world political and governing organizations.
 
'The Human Union Movement' is also a call for a new global political organization. This concept, introduced by Dr. Lyndon Storey, Ph.D. whom has developed the political and academic arguement for such a body. 

=Description=

The ideal of Human Union promotes exalting a 'win win' mutual ethic in all forms of commerce, distribution, and ideological struggle. Many of the concepts of Human Union are inspired by R.Buckminster Fuller, inventor of the World Game.

'Human Union', or something like it, may be nothing more than the result of the historical dialectic spoken of by Hegel and this arguement for the Human Union is found inside of a newly formed dialectic, called [[OS 0 1 2]] or sometimes ternary dialectics, which also promotes the idea of Human Union on it's website.

The Human Union Movement essentially centers around a concept Dr. Storey  refers to as 'potentialism' or the basic right of human beings to access their full potential. According to Dr. Storey, this basic and shared human quality must emerge into a new political party that acknowledges this universal princaple.


